{{infobox language |name=Lingling |nativename=Linghua |states=China |region=[[Guangxi]] |ethnicity=[[Miao people|Miao]] |speakers=20,000 |date=1991 |ref={{cn|date=August 2013}} |familycolor=mixed |family=[[mixed language|mixed]] [[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]]–[[Miao languages|Miao]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Lingling''' (Chinese: '''Ling hua''' 伶话 ''línghuà'' or '''Lingling hua'''; Lingling: ''{{IPA|liŋ˥ va˧}}'') is an unclassified mixed [[Chinese language|Chinese]] dialect. It is spoken by 20,000 ethnic [[Miao people|Miao]] in [[Longsheng]] County, [[Guangxi]]. It is only spoken within the community; with outsiders, [[Southwestern Mandarin]] is spoken.
