Rensch revised the reconstruction work of Longacre.  He revised the probable phonological inventory and described some of his proposals, based on comparisons of the cognates in the Mixtecan languages.  After this work, he proposed a reconstruction of the phonological system of Proto-Mixtecan.<ref>Rensch, 1977: 59.</ref> This proposal contains sixteen consonants, four vowels, and four tones.

